		{
			"name":"Checks & Triggers",
			"type":"feat",
			"img":"icons/svg/trap.svg",
			"system":{
				"description":{
					"value":"<p><b>Perception</b><br><ul><li>DC 20: Just before a character enters the statue's attack area, the character notices that the statue moves slightly, as if it were ready to pounce.</li><li>DC 25: The character notices a group of spidery runes carved lightly on the statue's base.</li></ul></p><p><b>Arcana</b><br><ul><li>DC 25: The character realizes that the statue is made with the help of magic, and it might be dangerous or even animate in nature.</li><li>DC 28: An Arcana check to detect magic sees an arcane aura that surrounds the trap (5 squares in every direction) and recognizes that this might be a trigger area for an effect.</li></ul></p><p><b>Trigger</b><br>When an enemy enters the magical aura radiating 5 squares around the statue, the statue animates and attacks that creature with the following attack, but as an immediate reaction instead of a standard action. Then roll for the statue's initiative. It acts each round on that turn, until no creature is within its trigger area.</p>",
